text: Yonah may refer to: * Yonah is the English transliteration for Jonah (יונה) in Hebrew and means dove. * Rabbi Yonah Gerondi * Yonah may be a typo for Yona * Yonah means bear in Cherokee * The Yonah (locomotive), one of the four steam locomotives involved in the Great Locomotive Chase during the American Civil War * Yonah Mountain, a mountain in northern Georgia, United States * Lake Yonah, on the Georgia – South Carolina border in the United States of America. * A Jewish bakery in Manhattan called Yonah Shimmel's Knish Bakery that has served fresh, oven-baked traditional Jewish delicacies since 1890 * Yonah (microprocessor), code name for a processor in Intel's Pentium M line, branded Intel Core * Yonah, Georgia
title: Yonah
